│ despite a legitimate cost-model disagreement due to simplifications only      │
│ present (or relevant) in vector form.\nThus the unconditional 'true' is       │
│ wrong; the predicate must depend on whether the VF under consideration is     │
│ vector or scalar (BestFactor.Width.isVector()). The function currently has no │
│ way to know which VF is being validated; computeBestVF passes no VF info. We  │
│ must extend planContainsAdditionalSimplifications to take a flag (or VF)      │
│ indicating whether to treat vector-specific ignored instructions.\n\n4.       │
│ Proposed Edit Points(s):\nEdit Point 1 (lines 7286-7333): Modify the          │
│ signature of planContainsAdditionalSimplifications to accept a bool IsVector  │
│ (or ElementCount VF) and use that instead of hard-coded 'true'.               │
│ Change:\nstatic bool planContainsAdditionalSimplifications(VPlan &Plan,       │
│ VPCostContext &CostCtx, Loop *TheLoop)\nTo:\nstatic bool                      │
│ planContainsAdditionalSimplifications(VPlan &Plan, VPCostContext &CostCtx,    │
